#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15954
msgid "\"<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>\": DSA key for SSH-2 (deprecated because it is slow.)"
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>PubkeyAuthentication</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;: clé DSA pour SSH-2 (obsolète parce qu'elle est lente)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15958
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ssh-keygen -t dsa\n"
"$ cat .ssh/id_dsa.pub | ssh user1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""
msgstr ""
"$ ssh-keygen -t dsa\n"
"$ cat .ssh/id_dsa.pub | ssh user1@remote \"cat - &gt;&gt;.ssh/authorized_keys\""

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15961
msgid "Use of DSA key for SSH-2 is deprecated because key is smaller and slow. There are no more reasons to work around RSA patent using DSA since it has been expired.  DSA stands for <ulink url=\"&digitalsignaturealgorithm;\">Digital Signature Algorithm</ulink> and slow. Also see <ulink url=\"&dsabfhbb;\">DSA-1571-1</ulink>."
msgstr "L’utilisation de clés DSA pour SSH-2 est obsolète parce que la clé est plus courte et lente. Il n'y a plus de raison de contourner le brevet de RSA en utilisant DSA parce qu'il est arrivé en fin de validité. DSA signifie <ulink url=\"&digitalsignaturealgorithm;\">Digital Signature Algorithm</ulink> (Algorithme de signature numérique) et il est lent. Voir aussi <ulink url=\"&dsabfhbb;\">DSA-1571-1</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:15964
msgid "For \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" to work in SSH-2, you must adjust the settings of \"<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>\" to \"<literal>yes</literal>\" in both \"<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>\" on the server host and \"<literal>/etc/ssh/ssh_config</literal>\" or \"<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>\" on the client host."
msgstr "Pour que «&nbsp;<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>&nbsp;» fonctionne avec SSH-2, vous devez définir les paramètres de «&nbsp;<literal>HostbasedAuthentication</literal>&nbsp;» à «&nbsp;<literal>yes</literal>&nbsp;» à la fois dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/ssh/sshd_config</literal>&nbsp;» sur la machine serveur et dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/ssh/ssh_config</literal>&nbsp;» ou «&nbsp;<literal>~/.ssh/config</literal>&nbsp;» sur la machine client."

