#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20315
msgid "Tracing program activities"
msgstr "Tracer l’activité d'un programme"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20316
msgid "You can trace program activity with <literal>strace</literal>(1), <literal>ltrace</literal>(1), or <literal>xtrace</literal>(1) for system calls and signals, library calls, or communication between X11 client and server."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tracer l’activité d'un programme avec <literal>strace</literal>(1), <literal>ltrace</literal>(1) ou <literal>xtrace</literal>(1) pour les appels système, les appels bibliothèque ou la communication entre le serveur et le client X11."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20317
msgid "You can trace system calls of the <literal>ls</literal> command as the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tracer les appels système  de la commande <literal>ls</literal> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20318
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo strace ls"
msgstr "$ sudo strace ls"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20321
msgid "Identification of processes using files or sockets"
msgstr "Identification des processus qui utilisent des fichiers ou des sockets"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20322
msgid "You can also identify processes using files by <literal>fuser</literal>(1), e.g. for \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi identifier les processus qui utilisent des fichiers par <literal>fuser</literal>(1), par exemple pour «&nbsp;<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>&nbsp;» en faisant ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20323
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo fuser -v /var/log/mail.log\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"/var/log/mail.log:   root       2946 F.... syslogd"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo fuser -v /var/log/mail.log\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"/var/log/mail.log:   root       2946 F.... syslogd"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20326
msgid "You see that file \"<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>\" is open for writing by the <literal>syslogd</literal>(8) command."
msgstr "Vous voyez que le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/var/log/mail.log</literal>&nbsp;» est ouvert en écriture par la commande <literal>syslogd</literal>(8)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20327
msgid "You can also identify processes using sockets by <literal>fuser</literal>(1), e.g. for \"<literal>smtp/tcp</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi identifier le processus qui utilisent des sockets par <literal>fuser</literal>(1), par exemple, pour «&nbsp;<literal>smtp/tcp</literal>&nbsp;» par ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20328
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sudo fuser -v smtp/tcp\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"smtp/tcp:            Debian-exim   3379 F.... exim4"
msgstr ""
"$ sudo fuser -v smtp/tcp\n"
"                     USER        PID ACCESS COMMAND\n"
"smtp/tcp:            Debian-exim   3379 F.... exim4"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20331
msgid "Now you know your system runs <literal>exim4</literal>(8) to handle <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink> connections to <ulink url=\"&smtp;\">SMTP</ulink> port (25)."
msgstr "Vous savez maintenant que <literal>exim4</literal>(8) tourne sur votre système pour gérer les connexions <ulink url=\"&tcp;\">TCP</ulink> du port <ulink url=\"&smtp;\">SMTP</ulink> (25)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:20334
