msgstr "tunnelez-la par <ulink url=\"&vpn;\">VPN</ulink>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23551
msgid "Limit it behind the secure firewall"
msgstr "limitez-la derrière une parefeu sûr"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23555
msgid "See also <xref linkend=\"_other_network_application_servers\"/> and <xref linkend=\"_other_network_application_clients\"/>."
msgstr "voir aussi <xref linkend=\"_other_network_application_servers\"/> et <xref linkend=\"_other_network_application_clients\"/>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23558
msgid "Archive media"
msgstr "Support d'archive"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23559
msgid "When choosing <ulink url=\"&computerdatastoragemedia;\">computer data storage media</ulink> for important data archive, you should be careful about their limitations.  For small personal data backup, I use CD-R and DVD-R by the brand name company and store in a cool, shaded, dry, clean environment.  (Tape archive media seem to be popular for professional use.)"
msgstr "Lors du choix d'un <ulink url=\"&computerdatastoragemedia;\">support d'enregistrement de données informatiques</ulink> destiné à l’archivage de données importantes, il faut faire attention à leurs limitations. Pour des petites sauvegardes de données personnelles, j'utilise des CD-R et des DVD-R provenant d'une grande marque et je les range dans un endroit frais, à l’ombre, sec et propre. (Les support d'archive sur bande semblent être populaires pour les utilisations professionnelles)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23561
msgid "<ulink url=\"&afireresistantsafe;\">A fire-resistant safe</ulink> are meant for paper documents.  Most of the computer data storage media have less temperature tolerance than paper. I usually rely on multiple secure encrypted copies stored in multiple secure locations."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&afireresistantsafe;\">Un coffre-fort anti-feu</ulink> est destiné aux documents sur papier. La plupart des support de stockage de données informatiques ont une tolérance en température inférieure à celle du papier. J'utilise en général plusieurs copies chiffrées stockées dans différents endroits sûrs.."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23563
msgid "Optimistic storage life of archive media seen on the net (mostly from vendor info)."
msgstr "Durées de vie optimistes des moyens d'archivage trouvées sur le net (la plupart à partir d'informations des constructeurs)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23567
msgid "100+ years : Acid free paper with ink"
msgstr "100 ans et plus&nbsp;: papier non acide et encre"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23572
msgid "100 years : Optical storage (CD/DVD, CD/DVD-R)"
msgstr "100 ans&nbsp;: stockage optique (CD/DVD, CD/DVD-R)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23577
msgid "30 years : Magnetic storage (tape, floppy)"
msgstr "30 ans&nbsp;: supports magnétiques (bande, disquette)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23582
msgid "20 years : Phase change optical storage (CD-RW)"
msgstr "20 ans&nbsp;: disque optique à changement de phase (CD-RW)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23586
msgid "These do not count on the mechanical failures due to handling etc."
msgstr "Ceci ne prend pas en compte les défaillances mécaniques dues aux manipulations, etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23587
msgid "Optimistic write cycle of archive media seen on the net (mostly from vendor info)."
msgstr "Nombre de cycles d'écriture optimistes des moyens d'archivage trouvées sur le net (la plupart à partir d'informations des constructeurs)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23591
msgid "250,000+ cycles : Harddisk drive"
msgstr "plus de 250 000&nbsp;: disque dur"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23596
msgid "10,000+ cycles : Flash memory"
msgstr "plus de 10 000 cycles&nbsp;: mémoires Flash"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23601
msgid "1,000 cycles : CD/DVD-RW"
msgstr "1000 cycles&nbsp;: CD/DVD-RW"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23606
msgid "1 cycles : CD/DVD-R, paper"
msgstr "1 cycle&nbsp;: CD/DVD-R, papier"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23611
msgid "Figures of storage life and write cycle here should not be used for decisions on any critical data storage.  Please consult the specific product information provided by the manufacture."
msgstr "Ces chiffres de durée de vie et de nombre de cycles ne devront pas être utilisés pour des décisions concernant l’enregistrement de données critiques. Veuillez consulter les informations spécifiques au produit fournies par le constructeur."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23614
msgid "Since CD/DVD-R and paper have only 1 write cycle, they inherently prevent accidental data loss by overwriting.  This is advantage!"
msgstr "Comme les CD/DVD-R et le papier n'ont qu'un cycle d'écriture de 1, ils évitent de manière inhérente le risque de perte de données par écrasement. C'est un avantage&nbsp;:!"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23617
msgid "If you need fast and frequent backup of large amount of data, a hard disk on a remote host linked by a fast network connection, may be the only realistic option."
msgstr "Si vous devez faire des sauvegardes fréquentes et rapide d'un gros volume de données, un disque dur sur une liaison réseau à haute vitesse peut être la seule option réaliste."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23622
msgid "The disk image"
msgstr "Le fichier image du disque"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23623
msgid "Here, we discuss manipulations of the disk image.  See <xref linkend=\"_data_storage_tips\"/>, too."
msgstr "Nous discutons ici des manipulations sur l’image disque. Voir aussi <xref linkend=\"_data_storage_tips\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23625
msgid "Making the disk image file"
msgstr "Créer le fichier image du disque"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23626
msgid "The disk image file, \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\", of an unmounted device, e.g., the second SCSI drive \"<literal>/dev/sdb</literal>\", can be made using <literal>cp</literal>(1) or <literal>dd</literal>(1) by the following."
msgstr "Le fichier image du disque, «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» d'un périphérique non monté, par exemple, le second périphérique SCSI «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sdb</literal>&nbsp;» peut être créé en utilisant <literal>cp</literal>(1) ou <literal>dd</literal>(1) par ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23627
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cp /dev/sdb disk.img\n"
"# dd if=/dev/sdb of=disk.img"
msgstr ""
"# cp /dev/sdb disque.img\n"
"# dd if=/dev/sdb of=disque.img"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23629
msgid "The disk image of the traditional PC's <ulink url=\"&masterbootrecordmbr;\">master boot record (MBR)</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_disk_partition_configuration\"/>) which reside on the first sector on the primary IDE disk can be made by using <literal>dd</literal>(1) by the following."
msgstr "L’image disque du <ulink url=\"&masterbootrecordmbr;\">master boot record (MBR)</ulink> (secteur principal d'amorçage) (voir<xref linkend=\"_disk_partition_configuration\"/>) qui se trouve sur le premier secteur du disque primaire IDE peut être faite en utilisant <literal>dd</literal>(1) comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23630
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# dd if=/dev/hda of=mbr.img bs=512 count=1\n"
"# dd if=/dev/hda of=mbr-nopart.img bs=446 count=1\n"
"# dd if=/dev/hda of=mbr-part.img skip=446 bs=1 count=66"
msgstr ""
"# dd if=/dev/hda of=mbr.img bs=512 count=1\n"
"# dd if=/dev/hda of=mbr-nopart.img bs=446 count=1\n"
"# dd if=/dev/hda of=mbr-part.img skip=446 bs=1 count=66"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23636
msgid "\"<literal>mbr.img</literal>\": The MBR with the partition table"
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>mbr.img</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;: MBR avec la table des partitions"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23641
msgid "\"<literal>mbr-nopart.img</literal>\": The MBR without the partition table"
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>mbr-nopart.img</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;: MBR sans la table des partitions"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23646
msgid "\"<literal>part.img</literal>\": The partition table of the MBR only"
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>part.img</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;: table de partition du MBR seul"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23650
msgid "If you have a SCSI device (including the new serial ATA drive) as the boot disk, substitute \"<literal>/dev/hda</literal>\" with \"<literal>/dev/sda</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si vous avez un périphérique SCSI (y-compris les nouveaux disque de type serial ATA) comme disque d'amorçage, remplacez «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;» avec «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sda</literal>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23651
msgid "If you are making an image of a disk partition of the original disk, substitute \"<literal>/dev/hda</literal>\" with \"<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>\" etc."
msgstr "Si vous réalisez une image d'une partition de disque du disque d'origine, remplacez «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;» par «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda1</literal>&nbsp;», etc."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23654
msgid "Writing directly to the disk"
msgstr "Écrire directement sur le disque"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23655
msgid "The disk image file, \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" can be written to an unmounted device, e.g., the second SCSI drive \"<literal>/dev/sdb</literal>\" with matching size, by the following."
msgstr "Le fichier image du disque «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» peut être écrit vers un disque non monté, par exemple le second disque SCSI «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sdb</literal>&nbsp;» avec la taille correspondante par ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23656
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dd if=disk.img of=/dev/sdb"
msgstr "# dd if=disk.img of=/dev/sdb"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23657
msgid "Similarly, the disk partition image file, \"<literal>partition.img</literal>\" can be written to an unmounted partition, e.g., the first partition of the second SCSI drive \"<literal>/dev/sdb1</literal>\" with matching size, by the following."
msgstr "De la même manière, le fichier image de la partition du disque, «&nbsp;<literal>partition.img</literal>&nbsp;» peut être écrit sur une partition non montée, par exemple, la première partition du second disque SCSI  «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sdb1</literal>&nbsp;» avec la taille correspondante comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23658
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dd if=partition.img of=/dev/sdb1"
msgstr "# dd if=partition.img of=/dev/sdb1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23661
msgid "Mounting the disk image file"
msgstr "Monter le fichier image dur disque"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23662
msgid "The disk image \"<literal>partition.img</literal>\" containing a single partition image can be mounted and unmounted by using the <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">loop device</ulink> as follows."
msgstr "L’image disque «&nbsp;<literal>partition.img</literal>&nbsp;», qui contient une partition image unique, peut être monté et démonter en utilisant le <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">périphérique de rebouclage (loop device)</ulink> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23663
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# losetup -v -f partition.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop0\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0\n"
"# mount -t auto /dev/loop0 /mnt/loop0\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount /dev/loop0\n"
"# losetup -d /dev/loop0"
msgstr ""
"# losetup -v -f partition.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop0\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0\n"
"# mount -t auto /dev/loop0 /mnt/loop0\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount /dev/loop0\n"
"# losetup -d /dev/loop0"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23670
msgid "This can be simplified as follows."
msgstr "Ceci peut être simplifié de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23671
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0\n"
"# mount -t auto -o loop partition.img /mnt/loop0\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount partition.img"
msgstr ""
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0\n"
"# mount -t auto -o loop partition.img /mnt/loop0\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount partition.img"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23675
msgid "Each partition of the disk image \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" containing multiple partitions can be mounted by using the <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">loop device</ulink>.  Since the loop device does not manage partitions by default, we need to reset it as follows."
msgstr "Chaque partition de l’image disque «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» contenant plusieurs partitions peut être monté en utilisant le <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">périphérique de rebouclage (loop device)</ulink>. Comme, par défaut, le périphérique de rebouclage ne gère par par partitions, il faut le réinitialiser de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23676
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# modinfo -p loop # verify kernel capability\n"
"max_part:Maximum number of partitions per loop device\n"
"max_loop:Maximum number of loop devices\n"
"# losetup -a # verify nothing using the loop device\n"
"# rmmod loop\n"
"# modprobe loop max_part=16"
msgstr ""
"# modinfo -p loop # verify kernel capability\n"
"max_part:Maximum number of partitions per loop device\n"
"max_loop:Maximum number of loop devices\n"
"# losetup -a # verify nothing using the loop device\n"
"# rmmod loop\n"
"# modprobe loop max_part=16"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23682
msgid "Now, the loop device can manage up to 16 partitions."
msgstr "Maintenant, le périphérique de rebouclage peut gérer jusqu’à 16 partitions."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23683
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# losetup -v -f disk.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop0\n"
"# fdisk -l /dev/loop0\n"
"\n"
"Disk /dev/loop0: 5368 MB, 5368709120 bytes\n"
"255 heads, 63 sectors/track, 652 cylinders\n"
"Units = cylinders of 16065 * 512 = 8225280 bytes\n"
"Disk identifier: 0x452b6464\n"
"\n"
"      Device Boot      Start         End      Blocks   Id  System\n"
"/dev/loop0p1               1         600     4819468+  83  Linux\n"
"/dev/loop0p2             601         652      417690   83  Linux\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0p1\n"
"# mount -t ext3 /dev/loop0p1 /mnt/loop0p1\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"# mount -t ext3 /dev/loop0p2 /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount /dev/loop0p1\n"
"# umount /dev/loop0p2\n"
"# losetup -d /dev/loop0"
msgstr ""
"# losetup -v -f disk.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop0\n"
"# fdisk -l /dev/loop0\n"
"\n"
"Disk /dev/loop0: 5368 MB, 5368709120 bytes\n"
"255 heads, 63 sectors/track, 652 cylinders\n"
"Units = cylinders of 16065 * 512 = 8225280 bytes\n"
"Disk identifier: 0x452b6464\n"
"\n"
"      Device Boot      Start         End      Blocks   Id  System\n"
"/dev/loop0p1               1         600     4819468+  83  Linux\n"
"/dev/loop0p2             601         652      417690   83  Linux\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0p1\n"
"# mount -t ext3 /dev/loop0p1 /mnt/loop0p1\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"# mount -t ext3 /dev/loop0p2 /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount /dev/loop0p1\n"
"# umount /dev/loop0p2\n"
"# losetup -d /dev/loop0"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23703
msgid "Alternatively, similar effects can be done by using the <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">device mapper</ulink> devices created by <literal>kpartx</literal>(8) from the <literal>kpartx</literal> package as follows."
msgstr "En remplacement, des effets similaires peuvent être obtenus en utilisant les périphériques <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">device mapper</ulink> créés par <literal>kpartx</literal>(8) du paquet <literal>kpartx</literal> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23704
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# kpartx -a -v disk.img\n"
"...\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"# mount -t ext3 /dev/mapper/loop0p2 /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"...\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount /dev/mapper/loop0p2\n"
"...\n"
"# kpartx -d /mnt/loop0"
msgstr ""
"# kpartx -a -v disk.img\n"
"...\n"
"# mkdir -p /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"# mount -t ext3 /dev/mapper/loop0p2 /mnt/loop0p2\n"
"...\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# umount /dev/mapper/loop0p2\n"
"...\n"
"# kpartx -d /mnt/loop0"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23714
msgid "You can mount a single partition of such disk image with <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">loop device</ulink> using offset to skip <ulink url=\"&mbr;\">MBR</ulink> etc., too.  But this is more error prone."
msgstr "Vous pouvez monter une partition unique d'une telle image de disque avec le <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">périphérique de rebouclage</ulink> en utilisant un décalage pour sauter le <ulink url=\"&mbr;\">MBR</ulink> ou autre. Mais ceci est susceptible d'induire des erreurs."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23718
msgid "Cleaning a disk image file"
msgstr "Nettoyage d'un fichier image du disque"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23719
msgid "A disk image file, \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" can be cleaned of all removed files into clean sparse image \"<literal>new.img</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "Un fichier image disque «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» peut être nettoyé de tous les fichiers supprimés pour donner une image propre «&nbsp;<literal>new.img</literal>&nbsp;» de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23720
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# mkdir old; mkdir new\n"
"# mount -t auto -o loop disk.img old\n"
"# dd bs=1 count=0 if=/dev/zero of=new.img seek=5G\n"
"# mount -t auto -o loop new.img new\n"
"# cd old\n"
"# cp -a --sparse=always ./ ../new/\n"
"# cd ..\n"
"# umount new.img\n"
"# umount disk.img"
msgstr ""
"# mkdir old; mkdir new\n"
"# mount -t auto -o loop disk.img old\n"
"# dd bs=1 count=0 if=/dev/zero of=new.img seek=5G\n"
"# mount -t auto -o loop new.img new\n"
"# cd old\n"
"# cp -a --sparse=always ./ ../new/\n"
"# cd ..\n"
"# umount new.img\n"
"# umount disk.img"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23729
msgid "If \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" is in ext2 or ext3, you can also use <literal>zerofree</literal>(8) from the <literal>zerofree</literal> package as follows."
msgstr "Si «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» est un système de fichier ext2 ou ext3, vous pouvez aussi utiliser <literal>zerofree</literal>(8) du paquet <literal>zerofree</literal> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23730
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# losetup -f -v disk.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop3\n"
"# zerofree /dev/loop3\n"
"# cp --sparse=always disk.img new.img"
msgstr ""
"# losetup -f -v disk.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop3\n"
"# zerofree /dev/loop3\n"
"# cp --sparse=always disk.img new.img"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23736
msgid "Making the empty disk image file"
msgstr "Réaliser le fichier image d'un disque vide"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23737
msgid "The empty disk image \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" which can grow up to 5GiB can be made using <literal>dd</literal>(1) as follows."
msgstr "Le fichier image du disque vide «&nbsp;<literal>sparse</literal>&nbsp;», qui pourra s'étendre jusqu'à 5Gio peut être faite en utilisant <literal>dd</literal>(1) et <literal>mke2fs</literal>(8) comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23738
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ dd bs=1 count=0 if=/dev/zero of=disk.img seek=5G"
msgstr "$ dd bs=1 count=0 if=/dev/zero of=disk.img seek=5G"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23739
msgid "You can create an ext3 filesystem on this disk image \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" using the <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">loop device</ulink> as follows."
msgstr "Vous pouvez créer un système de fichiers ext3 sur cette image disque «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» en utilisant le <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">périphérique de rebouclage (loop device)</ulink> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23740
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# losetup -f -v disk.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop1\n"
"# mkfs.ext3 /dev/loop1\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# losetup -d /dev/loop1\n"
"$ du  --apparent-size -h disk.img\n"
"5.0G  disk.img\n"
"$ du -h disk.img\n"
"83M disk.img"
msgstr ""
"# losetup -f -v disk.img\n"
"Loop device is /dev/loop1\n"
"# mkfs.ext3 /dev/loop1\n"
"...hack...hack...hack\n"
"# losetup -d /dev/loop1\n"
"$ du  --apparent-size -h disk.img\n"
"5.0G  disk.img\n"
"$ du -h disk.img\n"
"83M disk.img"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23749
msgid "For \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\", its file size is 5.0 GiB and its actual disk usage is mere 83MiB.  This discrepancy is possible since <ulink url=\"&extcfs;\">ext2fs</ulink> can hold <ulink url=\"&sparsefile;\">sparse file</ulink>."
msgstr "Pour «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;», sa taille de fichier de 5.0 Gio et son utilisation disque est uniquement de 83Mio. Cette discordance est possible car <ulink url=\"&extcfs;\">ext2fs</ulink> sait maintenir un <ulink url=\"&sparsefile;\">fichier sparse</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23751
msgid "The actual disk usage of <ulink url=\"&sparsefile;\">sparse file</ulink> grows with data which are written to it."
msgstr "L’utilisation réelle sur le disque du <ulink url=\"&sparsefile;\">fichier sparse</ulink> croît au fur et à mesure qu'on y écrit des données ."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23753
msgid "Using similar operation on devices created by the <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">loop device</ulink> or the <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">device mapper</ulink> devices as <xref linkend=\"_mounting_the_disk_image_file\"/>, you can partition this disk image \"<literal>disk.img</literal>\" using <literal>parted</literal>(8) or <literal>fdisk</literal>(8), and can create filesystem on it using <literal>mkfs.ext3</literal>(8), <literal>mkswap</literal>(8), etc."
msgstr "En utilisant des opérations similaires sur les périphériques créés par <ulink url=\"&loopdevice;\">loop device</ulink> ou les périphériques <ulink url=\"&devicemapper;\">device mapper</ulink> comme dans <xref linkend=\"_mounting_the_disk_image_file\"/>, vous pouvez partitionner cette image disque «&nbsp;<literal>disk.img</literal>&nbsp;» en utilisant <literal>parted</literal>(8) ou <literal>fdisk</literal>(8), et y créer un système de fichiers en utilisant <literal>mkfs.ext3</literal>(8), <literal>mkswap</literal>(8), etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23756
msgid "Making the ISO9660 image file"
msgstr "Créer le fichier image ISO9660"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23757
msgid "The <ulink url=\"&isojgga;\">ISO9660</ulink> image file, \"<literal>cd.iso</literal>\", from the source directory tree at \"<literal>source_directory</literal>\" can be made using <literal>genisoimage</literal>(1) provided by <ulink url=\"&cdrkit;\">cdrkit</ulink> by the following."
msgstr "On peut faire le fichier image <ulink url=\"&isojgga;\">ISO9660</ulink>, «&nbsp;<literal>cd.iso</literal>&nbsp;», depuis l’arborescence de répertoire source située à «&nbsp;<literal>répertoire_source</literal>&nbsp;», en utilisant <literal>genisoimage</literal>(1) fourni par<ulink url=\"&cdrkit;\">cdrkit</ulink> de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23758
#, no-wrap
msgid "#  genisoimage -r -J -T -V volume_id -o cd.iso source_directory"
msgstr "#  genisoimage -r -J -T -V volume_id -o cd.iso répertoire_source"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23759
msgid "Similarly, the bootable ISO9660 image file, \"<literal>cdboot.iso</literal>\", can be made from <literal>debian-installer</literal> like directory tree at \"<literal>source_directory</literal>\" by the following."
msgstr "De la même manière, on peut créer le fichier image ISO9660 amorçable <literal>«&nbsp;cdboot.iso</literal>&nbsp;» depuis une arborescence comme celle de <literal>debian-installer</literal> située en «&nbsp;<literal>source_directory</literal>&nbsp;», de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23760
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#  genisoimage -r -o cdboot.iso -V volume_id \\\n"
"   -b isolinux/isolinux.bin -c isolinux/boot.cat \\\n"
"   -no-emul-boot -boot-load-size 4 -boot-info-table source_directory"
msgstr ""
"#  genisoimage -r -o cdboot.iso -V volume_id \\\n"
"   -b isolinux/isolinux.bin -c isolinux/boot.cat \\\n"
"   -no-emul-boot -boot-load-size 4 -boot-info-table répertoire_source"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23763
msgid "Here <ulink url=\"&isolinuxbootloader;\">Isolinux boot loader</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_stage_2_the_boot_loader\"/>) is used for booting."
msgstr "Ici, le <ulink url=\"&isolinuxbootloader;\">chargeur d'amorçage Isolinux</ulink> (voir <xref linkend=\"_stage_2_the_boot_loader\"/>) est utilisé pour l’amorçage."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23764
msgid "You can calculate the md5sum value and make the ISO9660 image directly from the CD-ROM device as follows."
msgstr "Vous pouvez calculer la valeur de la somme md5 (md5sum) et construire des image ISO9660 directement depuis un lecteur de CD-ROM de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23765
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ isoinfo -d -i /dev/cdrom\n"
"CD-ROM is in ISO 9660 format\n"
"...\n"
"Logical block size is: 2048\n"
"Volume size is: 23150592\n"
"...\n"
"# dd if=/dev/cdrom bs=2048 count=23150592 conv=notrunc,noerror | md5sum\n"
"# dd if=/dev/cdrom bs=2048 count=23150592 conv=notrunc,noerror &gt; cd.iso"
msgstr ""
"$ isoinfo -d -i /dev/cdrom\n"
"CD-ROM is in ISO 9660 format\n"
"...\n"
"Logical block size is: 2048\n"
"Volume size is: 23150592\n"
"...\n"
"# dd if=/dev/cdrom bs=2048 count=23150592 conv=notrunc,noerror | md5sum\n"
"# dd if=/dev/cdrom bs=2048 count=23150592 conv=notrunc,noerror &gt; cd.iso"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23774
msgid "You must carefully avoid ISO9660 filesystem read ahead bug of Linux as above to get the right result."
msgstr "Vous devrez prendre garde à éviter le bogue de lecture anticipée du système de fichiers ISO9660 de Linux comme ci-dessus afin d’obtenir les résultats corrects."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23778
msgid "Writing directly to the CD/DVD-R/RW"
msgstr "Écriture directe sur CD/DVD-R/RW"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23780
msgid "DVD is only a large CD to <literal>wodim</literal>(1) provided by <ulink url=\"&cdrkit;\">cdrkit</ulink>."
msgstr "Un DVD n'est qu'un gros CD pour <literal>wodim</literal>(1) qui est fourni par <ulink url=\"&cdrkit;\">cdrkit</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23782
msgid "You can find a usable device by the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez rechercher un périphérique utilisable comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23783
#, no-wrap
msgid "# wodim --devices"
msgstr "# wodim --devices"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23784
msgid "Then the blank CD-R is inserted to the CD drive, and the ISO9660 image file, \"<literal>cd.iso</literal>\" is written to this device, e.g., \"<literal>/dev/hda</literal>\", using <literal>wodim</literal>(1) by the following."
msgstr "Le CD-R vierge est alors inséré dans le graveur de CD et le fichier image ISO9660 «&nbsp;<literal>cd.iso</literal>&nbsp;» est écrit vers le périphérique, par exemple; «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;» en utilisant <literal>wodim</literal>(1) de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23785
#, no-wrap
msgid "# wodim -v -eject dev=/dev/hda cd.iso"
msgstr "# wodim -v -eject dev=/dev/hda cd.iso"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23786
msgid "If CD-RW is used instead of CD-R, do this instead by the following."
msgstr "Si un CD-RW est utilisé à la place d'un CD-R, faites alors ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23787
#, no-wrap
msgid "# wodim -v -eject blank=fast dev=/dev/hda cd.iso"
msgstr "# wodim -v -eject blank=fast dev=/dev/hda cd.iso"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23789
msgid "If your desktop system mounts CD automatically, unmount it by \"<literal>sudo unmount /dev/hda</literal>\" before using <literal>wodim</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Si votre système de bureau monte automatiquement les CD, démontez-le par la commande «&nbsp;<literal>sudo unmount /dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;» avant d'utiliser <literal>wodim</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23793
msgid "Mounting the ISO9660 image file"
msgstr "Monter le fichier image ISO9660"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23794
msgid "If \"<literal>cd.iso</literal>\" contains an ISO9660 image, then the following manually mounts it to \"<literal>/cdrom</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si «&nbsp;<literal>cd.iso</literal>&nbsp;» contient une image ISO9660, ce qui suit permet alors de le monter manuellement sur «&nbsp;<literal>/cdrom</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23795
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mount -t iso9660 -o ro,loop cd.iso /cdrom"
msgstr "# mount -t iso9660 -o ro,loop cd.iso /cdrom"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:23797
msgid "Modern desktop system mounts removable media automatically (see <xref linkend=\"_removable_storage_device\"/>)."
msgstr "Les systèmes de bureau modernes montent automatiquement les supports amovibles (voir <xref linkend=\"_removable_storage_device\"/>)."

