#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24182
msgid "When a data is too big to backup as a single file, you can backup its content after splitting it into, e.g. 2000MiB chunks and merge those chunks back into the original file later."
msgstr "Lorsque les données ont un volume trop important pour pouvoir être sauvegardée dans un seul fichier, vous pouvez en sauvegarder le contenu après l’avoir éclaté en morceaux de, par exemple, 2000Mio et réassembler ces morceaux par la suite sous la forme du fichier d'origine."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ split -b 2000m large_file\n"
"$ cat x* &gt;large_file"
msgstr ""
"$ split -b 2000m gros_fichier\n"
"$ cat x* &gt;gros_fichier"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24186
msgid "Please make sure you do not have any files starting with \"<literal>x</literal>\" to avoid name crashes."
msgstr "Assurez-vous ne pas pas avoir de nom de fichier commençant par «&nbsp;<literal>x</literal>&nbsp;» afin d'éviter des plantages de nom."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24190
msgid "Clearing file contents"
msgstr "Effacer le contenu d'un fichier"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24191
msgid "In order to clear the contents of a file such as a log file, do not use <literal>rm</literal>(1) to delete the file and then create a new empty file, because the file may still be accessed in the interval between commands.  The following is the safe way to clear the contents of the file."
msgstr "Pour effacer le contenu d'un fichier comme, par exemple, un fichier journal, n'utilisez pas la commande <literal>rm</literal>(1) pour supprimer le fichier et recréer ensuite un fichier vide parce qu'on peut encore accéder au fichier dans l’intervalle entre les commandes. Voici est la manière sûre d'effacer le contenu d'un fichier&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24192
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ :&gt;file_to_be_cleared"
msgstr "$ :&gt;fichier_a_effacer"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24195
msgid "Dummy files"
msgstr "Fichiers fictifs"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24196
msgid "The following commands create dummy or empty files."
msgstr "Les commandes suivantes créent des fichiers factices ou vides."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ dd if=/dev/zero    of=5kb.file bs=1k count=5\n"
"$ dd if=/dev/urandom of=7mb.file bs=1M count=7\n"
"$ touch zero.file\n"
"$ : &gt; alwayszero.file"
msgstr ""
"$ dd if=/dev/zero    of=5kb.file bs=1k count=5\n"
"$ dd if=/dev/urandom of=7mb.file bs=1M count=7\n"
"$ touch zero.file\n"
"$ : &gt; alwayszero.file"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24201
msgid "You should find following files."
msgstr "Vous obtiendrez les fichiers suivants&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24205
msgid "\"<literal>5kb.file</literal>\" is 5KB of zeros."
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>5kb.file</literal>&nbsp;» avec 5K de zéros&nbsp;;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24210
msgid "\"<literal>7mb.file</literal>\" is 7MB of random data."
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>7mb.file</literal>&nbsp;» avec 7Mo de données aléatoires&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24215
msgid "\"<literal>zero.file</literal>\" may be a 0 byte file.  If it existed, its <literal>mtime</literal> is updated while its content and its length are kept."
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>zero.file</literal>&nbsp;» devrait être un fichier de 0 octet. S'il existait, son <literal>mtime</literal> est mis à jour alors que son contenu et sa taille sont conservés&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24220
msgid "\"<literal>alwayszero.file</literal>\" is always a 0 byte file.  If it existed, its <literal>mtime</literal> is updated and its content is reset."
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>alwayszero.file</literal>&nbsp; fait toujours 0 octet. S'il existait son <literal>mtime</literal> est mis à jour et son contenu vidé."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24226
msgid "Erasing an entire hard disk"
msgstr "Effacer l’ensemble du disque dur"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24227
msgid "There are several ways to completely erase data from an entire hard disk like device, e.g., USB memory stick at \"<literal>/dev/sda</literal>\"."
msgstr "Il existe plusieurs manière d'effacer complètement les données d'un périphérique semblable à disque dur, par exemple, une clé USB se trouvant en «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sda</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24229
msgid "Check your USB memory stick location with <literal>mount</literal>(8) first before executing commands here.  The device pointed by \"<literal>/dev/sda</literal>\" may be SCSI hard disk or serial-ATA hard disk where your entire system resides."
msgstr "Vérifiez d'abord l’emplacement de votre clé USB avec <literal>mount</literal>(8) avant d'exécuter ces commandes. Le périphérique pointé par «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sda</literal>&nbsp;» peut être le disque dur SCSI ou un disque dur SATA sur lequel se trouve l’ensemble de votre système."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24231
msgid "Erase all the disk content by resetting data to 0 with the following."
msgstr "Effacer tout le contenu du disque en réinitialisant toutes les données à 0 avec la commande suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24232
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sda"
msgstr "# dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sda"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24233
msgid "Erase all by overwriting random data with the following."
msgstr "Tout effacer en écrasant les données existantes par des données aléatoires par la commande suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24234
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dd if=/dev/urandom of=/dev/sda"
msgstr "# dd if=/dev/urandom of=/dev/sda"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24235
msgid "Erase all by overwriting random data very efficiently with the following."
msgstr "Effacer de manière très efficace toutes les données en les écrasant avec des données aléatoires par la commande suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24236
#, no-wrap
msgid "# shred -v -n 1 /dev/sda"
msgstr "# shred -v -n 1 /dev/sda"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24237
msgid "Since <literal>dd</literal>(1) is available from the shell of many bootable Linux CDs such as Debian installer CD, you can erase your installed system completely by running an erase command from such media on the system hard disk, e.g., \"<literal>/dev/hda</literal>\", \"<literal>/dev/sda</literal>\", etc."
msgstr "Comme <literal>dd</literal>(1) est disponible depuis l’interpréteur de commandes de nombreux CD amorçables de Linux tels que le CD de l’installateur Debian, vous pouvez effacer complètement votre système installé en lançant la commande d'effacement du disque du disque dur du système, par exemple, «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/hda</literal>&nbsp;», «&nbsp;<literal>/dev/sda</literal>&nbsp;», etc. depuis un tel support, "

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24240
msgid "Erasing unused area of an hard disk"
msgstr "Effacer l’ensemble du disque dur"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24241
msgid "Unused area on an hard disk (or USB memory stick), e.g. \"<literal>/dev/sdb1</literal>\" may still contain erased data themselves since they are only unlinked from the filesystem.  These can be cleaned by overwriting them."
msgstr "Une zone inutilisée du disque dur (ou d’une clé mémoire USB), par ex. «&nbsp;<literal>/devsdb1</literal>&nbsp;» peut encore contenir les données effacées elles-mêmes puisque elle ne sont que déliées du système de fichiers. Elles peuvent être nettoyées en les surchargeant."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24242
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# mount -t auto /dev/sdb1 /mnt/foo\n"
"# cd /mnt/foo\n"
"# dd if=/dev/zero of=junk\n"
"dd: writing to `junk': No space left on device\n"
"...\n"
"# sync\n"
"# umount /dev/sdb1"
msgstr ""
"# mount -t auto /dev/sdb1 /mnt/foo\n"
"# cd /mnt/foo\n"
"# dd if=/dev/zero of=junk\n"
"dd: writing to `junk': No space left on device\n"
"...\n"
"# sync\n"
"# umount /dev/sdb1"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24250
msgid "This is usually a good enough for your USB memory stick.  But this is not perfect.  Most parts of erased filenames and their attributes may be hidden and remain in the filesystem."
msgstr "Ceci est en général suffisamment bon pour votre clé mémoire USB. Mais ce n’est pas parfait. La plupart des noms des fichiers effacés et leurs attributs peut être cachés et restés dans le système de fichiers."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24254
msgid "Undeleting deleted but still open files"
msgstr "Récupérer des fichiers supprimés mais encore ouverts"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24255
msgid "Even if you have accidentally deleted a file, as long as that file is still being used by some application (read or write mode), it is possible to recover such a file."
msgstr "Même si vous avez accidentellement supprimé un fichier, tant que ce fichier est en cours d'utilisation par une application quelconque, (en mode lecture ou écriture); il est possible de récupérer un tel fichier."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ echo foo &gt; bar\n"
"$ less bar\n"
"$ ps aux | grep ' less[ ]'\n"
"bozo    4775  0.0  0.0  92200   884 pts/8    S+   00:18   0:00 less bar\n"
"$ rm bar\n"
"$ ls -l /proc/4775/fd | grep bar\n"
"lr-x------ 1 bozo bozo 64 2008-05-09 00:19 4 -&gt; /home/bozo/bar (deleted)\n"
"$ cat /proc/4775/fd/4 &gt;bar\n"
"$ ls -l\n"
"-rw-r--r-- 1 bozo bozo 4 2008-05-09 00:25 bar\n"
"$ cat bar\n"
"foo"
msgstr ""
"$ echo toto &gt; titi\n"
"$ less titi\n"
"$ ps aux | grep ' less[ ]'\n"
"bozo    4775  0.0  0.0  92200   884 pts/8    S+   00:18   0:00 less titi\n"
"$ rm titi\n"
"$ ls -l /proc/4775/fd | grep titi\n"
"lr-x------ 1 bozo bozo 64 2008-05-09 00:19 4 -&gt; /home/bozo/titi (deleted)\n"
"$ cat /proc/4775/fd/4 &gt;titi\n"
"$ ls -l\n"
"-rw-r--r-- 1 bozo bozo 4 2008-05-09 00:25 titi\n"
"$ cat titir\n"
"toto"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24269
msgid "Execute on another terminal (when you have the <literal>lsof</literal> package installed) as follows."
msgstr "Exécutez sur une autre terminal (lorsque vous avez le paquet <literal>lsof</literal>installé) comme suit"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:24270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ls -li bar\n"
"2228329 -rw-r--r-- 1 bozo bozo 4 2008-05-11 11:02 bar\n"
"$ lsof |grep bar|grep less\n"
"less 4775 bozo 4r REG 8,3 4 2228329 /home/bozo/bar\n"
"$ rm bar\n"
"$ lsof |grep bar|grep less\n"
"less 4775 bozo 4r REG 8,3 4 2228329 /home/bozo/bar (deleted)\n"
"$ cat /proc/4775/fd/4 &gt;bar\n"
"$ ls -li bar\n"
"2228302 -rw-r--r-- 1 bozo bozo 4 2008-05-11 11:05 bar\n"
"$ cat bar\n"
"foo"
msgstr ""
"$ ls -li titi\n"
"2228329 -rw-r--r-- 1 bozo bozo 4 2008-05-11 11:02 titi\n"
"$ lsof |grep titi|grep less\n"
"less 4775 bozo 4r REG 8,3 4 2228329 /home/bozo/titi\n"
"$ rm titi\n"
"$ lsof |grep titi|grep less\n"
"less 4775 bozo 4r REG 8,3 4 2228329 /home/bozo/titi (deleted)\n"
"$ cat /proc/4775/fd/4 &gt;titi\n"
"$ ls -li titi\n"
"2228302 -rw-r--r-- 1 bozo bozo 4 2008-05-11 11:05 titi\n"
"$ cat titi\n"
"toto"

