#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26315
msgid "With <literal>git</literal>(1), you work on a local branch with many commits and use something like \"<literal>git rebase -i master</literal>\" to reorganize change history later. This enables you to make clean change history.  See <literal>git-rebase</literal>(1) and <literal>git-cherry-pick</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Avec <literal>git</literal>(1), vous travaillez sur une branche locale avec de nombreuses commit et vous utilisez quelque chose comme «&nbsp;<literal>git rebase -i master</literal>&nbsp;» pour réorganiser plus tard l’historique des modifications. Ceci vous permet de faire des modifications propre de l’historique. Voir <literal>git-rebase</literal>(1) et <literal>git-cherry-pick</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26318
msgid "When you want to go back to a clean working directory without loosing the current state of the working directory, you can use \"<literal>git stash</literal>\".  See <literal>git-stash</literal>(1)."
msgstr "Si vous désirez retrouver un répertoire propre sans perdre l’état actuel du répertoire de travail, vous pouvez utiliser «&nbsp;<literal>git stash</literal>&nbsp;». Voir <literal>git-stash</literal>(1)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26322
msgid "Git for the Subversion repository"
msgstr "Git pour le dépôt Subversion"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26323
msgid "You can check out a Subversion repository at \"<literal>svn+ssh://svn.example.org/project/module/trunk</literal>\" to a local Git repository at \"<literal>./dest</literal>\" and commit back to the Subversion repository.  E.g.:"
msgstr "Un dépôt Subversion en « <literal>svn+ssh://svn.example.org/project/module/trunk</literal> » peut être extrait vers un dépôt Git local en « <literal>./dest</literal> » puis renvoyé vers le dépôt subversion. Par exemple :"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26324
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ git svn clone -s -rHEAD svn+ssh://svn.example.org/project dest\n"
"$ cd dest\n"
"... make changes\n"
"$ git commit -a\n"
"... keep working locally with git\n"
"$ git svn dcommit"
msgstr ""
"$ git svn clone -s -rHEAD svn+ssh://svn.example.org/project dest\n"
"$ cd dest\n"
"... effectuer des modifications\n"
"$ git commit -a\n"
"... travailler encore avec git\n"
"$ git svn dcommit"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26331
msgid "The use of \"<literal>-rHEAD</literal>\" enables us to avoid cloning entire historical contents from the Subversion repository."
msgstr "L’utilisation de «&nbsp;<literal>rHEAD</literal>&nbsp;» nous permet d’éviter de devoir cloner l’ensemble du contenu de l’historique du dépôt Subversion."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26335
msgid "Git for recording configuration history"
msgstr "Git pour l’enregistrement de l’historique de la configuration"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26336
msgid "You can manually record chronological history of configuration using <ulink url=\"&git;\">Git</ulink> tools.  Here is a simple example for your practice to record \"<literal>/etc/apt/</literal>\" contents."
msgstr "Vous pouvez enregistrer vous-même un historique chronologique de la configuration en utilisant les outils <ulink url=\"&git;\">Git</ulink>. Voici un exemple simple, pour vous exercer, d'enregistrement du contenu de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/</literal>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26337
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd /etc/apt/\n"
"$ sudo git init\n"
"$ sudo chmod 700 .git\n"
"$ sudo git add .\n"
"$ sudo git commit -a"
msgstr ""
"$ cd /etc/apt/\n"
"$ sudo git init\n"
"$ sudo chmod 700 .git\n"
"$ sudo git add .\n"
"$ sudo git commit -a"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
