#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30848
msgid "Uninstall program"
msgstr "Désinstaller un programme"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30849
msgid "If you have the original source and if it uses <literal>autoconf</literal>(1)/<literal>automake</literal>(1) and if you can remember how you configured it, execute as follows to uninstall the program."
msgstr "Si vous avez les sources d'origine et s'ils utilisent <literal>autoconf</literal>(1) et <literal>automake</literal>(1) et si vous-vous souvenez comment vous l’avez configuré, exécutez-le comme suit pour désinstaller le programme&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30850
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ./configure \"all-of-the-options-you-gave-it\"\n"
"# make uninstall"
msgstr ""
"$ ./configure «&nbsp;toutes-les-options-que-vous-lui-avez-passé&nbsp;»\n"
"# make uninstall"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30852
msgid "Alternatively, if you are absolutely sure that the install process puts files only under \"<literal>/usr/local/</literal>\" and there is nothing important there, you can erase all its contents by the following."
msgstr "Sinon, si vous êtes absolument certain que le processus d'installation n'a mis des fichiers que sous «&nbsp;<literal>/usr/local/</literal>&nbsp;» et qu'il n'y a là rien d'important, vous pouvez supprimer tout son contenu avec&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30853
#, no-wrap
msgid "# find /usr/local -type f -print0 | xargs -0 rm -f"
msgstr "# find /usr/local -type f -print0 | xargs -0 rm -f"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30854
msgid "If you are not sure where files are installed, you should consider using <literal>checkinstall</literal>(8)  from the <literal>checkinstall</literal> package, which provides a clean path for the uninstall.  It now supports to create a Debian package with \"<literal>-D</literal>\" option."
msgstr "Si vous n'êtes pas certain de l’emplacement où les fichiers ont été installés, vous devriez envisager d'utiliser <literal>checkinstall</literal>(8)  du paquet <literal>checkinstall</literal> qui fournit une voie propre pour la désistallation. Il prend maintenant en charge la création d'un paquet Debian à l’aide de l’option «&nbsp;<literal>-D</literal>&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30858
msgid "Perl short script madness"
msgstr "Folie de courts scripts en Perl"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30859
msgid "Although any <ulink url=\"&awk;\">AWK</ulink> scripts can be automatically rewritten in <ulink url=\"&perl;\">Perl</ulink> using <literal>a2p</literal>(1), one-liner AWK scripts are best converted to one-liner Perl scripts manually."
msgstr "Bien que tous les scripts en <ulink url=\"&awk;\">AWK</ulink> puissent être réécrits automatiquement en <ulink url=\"&perl;\">Perl</ulink> en utilisant <literal>a2p</literal>(1), il est plus facile de convertir manuellement les scripts AWK constitués d'une seule ligne en scripts Perl d'une seule ligne."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30860
msgid "Let's think following AWK script snippet."
msgstr "Regardons le bout de script AWK suivant&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30861
#, no-wrap
msgid "awk '($2==\"1957\") { print $3 }' |"
msgstr "awk '($2==\"1957\") { print $3 }' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30862
msgid "This is equivalent to any one of the following lines."
msgstr "Il est équivalent à l’une quelconque des lignes suivantes&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30863
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -ne '@f=split; if ($f[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"
msgstr "perl -ne '@f=split; if ($f[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30864
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -ne 'if ((@f=split)[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"
msgstr "perl -ne 'if ((@f=split)[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30865
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -ne '@f=split; print $f[2] if ( $f[1]==1957 )' |"
msgstr "perl -ne '@f=split; print $f[2] if ( $f[1]==1957 )' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30866
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -lane 'print $F[2] if $F[1] eq \"1957\"' |"
msgstr "perl -lane 'print $F[2] if $F[1] eq \"1957\"' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30867
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -lane 'print$F[2]if$F[1]eq+1957' |"
msgstr "perl -lane 'print$F[2]if$F[1]eq+1957' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30868
msgid "The last one is a riddle.  It took advantage of following Perl features."
msgstr "La dernière est une devinette. Elle tire parti des fonctionnalités suivantes de Perl&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30872
msgid "The whitespace is optional."
msgstr "L’espace est optionnel."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30877
msgid "The automatic conversion exists from number to the string."
msgstr "Il existe une conversion automatique des nombres en chaîne de caractères."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30881
msgid "See <literal>perlrun</literal>(1) for the command-line options.  For more crazy Perl scripts, <ulink url=\"&perlgolf;\">Perl Golf</ulink> may be interesting."
msgstr "Voir <literal>perlrun</literal>(1) pour les options de la ligne de commandes. Pour des scripts en Perl plus fous, il peut être intéressant de consulter <ulink url=\"&perlgolf;\">Perl Golf</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30884
msgid "Web"
msgstr "Web"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30885
msgid "Basic interactive dynamic web pages can be made as follows."
msgstr "Des pages web dynamiques et interactives simples peuvent être faites de la manière suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30889
msgid "Queries are presented to the browser user using <ulink url=\"&html;\">HTML</ulink> forms."
msgstr "Les requêtes dont présentées au navigateur de l’utilisateur en utilisant des formulaires <ulink url=\"&html;\">HTML</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30894
msgid "Filling and clicking on the form entries sends one of the following <ulink url=\"&url;\">URL</ulink> string with encoded parameters from the browser to the web server."
msgstr "Remplir et cliquer les entrées de formulaires envoie une des chaînes d'<ulink url=\"&url;\">URL</ulink> suivantes avec des paramètres codés depuis le navigateur vers le serveur web."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30899
msgid "\"<literal>http://www.foo.dom/cgi-bin/program.pl?VAR1=VAL1&amp;VAR2=VAL2&amp;VAR3=VAL3</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>http://www.foo.dom/cgi-bin/programme.pl?VAR1=VAL1&amp;VAR2=VAL2&amp;VAR3=VAL3</literal>&nbsp;»"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30904
msgid "\"<literal>http://www.foo.dom/cgi-bin/program.py?VAR1=VAL1&amp;VAR2=VAL2&amp;VAR3=VAL3</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>http://www.foo.dom/cgi-bin/programme.py?VAR1=VAL1&amp;VAR2=VAL2&amp;VAR3=VAL3</literal>&nbsp;»"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30909
msgid "\"<literal>http://www.foo.dom/program.php?VAR1=VAL1&amp;VAR2=VAL2&amp;VAR3=VAL3</literal>\""
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>http://www.foo.dom/programme.php?VAR1=VAL1&amp;VAR2=VAL2&amp;VAR3=VAL3</literal>&nbsp;»"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30916
msgid "\"<literal>%nn</literal>\" in URL is replaced with a character with hexadecimal <literal>nn</literal> value."
msgstr "«&nbsp;<literal>%nn</literal>&nbsp;» dans l’URL est remplacé par le caractère dont la valeur hexadécimale est <literal>nn</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30921
msgid "The environment variable is set as: \"<literal>QUERY_STRING=\"VAR1=VAL1 VAR2=VAL2 VAR3=VAL3\"</literal>\"."
msgstr "La variable d'environnement est définie à&nbsp;: «&nbsp;<literal>QUERY_STRING=\"VAR1=VAL1 VAR2=VAL2 VAR3=VAL3\"</literal>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30925
msgid "<ulink url=\"&cgi;\">CGI</ulink> program (any one of \"<literal>program.*</literal>\") on the web server executes itself with the environment variable \"<literal>$QUERY_STRING</literal>\"."
msgstr "Le programme <ulink url=\"&cgi;\">CGI</ulink> (l’un quelconque des «&nbsp;<literal>programme.*</literal>&nbsp;») sur le serveur web s'exécute lui-même avec la variable d'environnement «&nbsp;<literal>$QUERY_STRING</literal>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30929
msgid "<literal>stdout</literal> of CGI program is sent to the web browser and is presented as an interactive dynamic web page."
msgstr "La <literal>sortie standard (stdout)</literal> du programme CGI est envoyée au navigateur web et présentée sous forme d'une page web dynamique interactive."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30933
msgid "For security reasons it is better not to hand craft new hacks for parsing CGI parameters.  There are established modules for them in Perl and Python.  <ulink url=\"&php;\">PHP</ulink> comes with these functionalities.  When client data storage is needed, <ulink url=\"&httpcookies;\">HTTP cookies</ulink> are used.  When client side data processing is needed, <ulink url=\"&javascript;\">Javascript</ulink> is frequently used."
msgstr "Pour des raisons de sécurité, il est préférable de ne pas réaliser soi-même de nouvelles bidouilles pour analyser les paramètres CGI. Il existe des modules bien établis pour cela, en Perl et Python. <ulink url=\"&php;\">PHP</ulink> est fourni avec ces fonctionnalités. Lorsqu'il est nécessaire d'enregistrer des données du client, on utilise des <ulink url=\"&httpcookies;\">cookies HTTP</ulink>. Lorsqu'un traitement de données est nécessaire côté client, on utilise fréquemment <ulink url=\"&javascript;\">Javascript</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30934
msgid "For more, see the <ulink url=\"&commongatewayinterface;\">Common Gateway Interface</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&theapachesoftwarefoundation;\">The Apache Software Foundation</ulink>, and <ulink url=\"&javascript;\">JavaScript</ulink>."
msgstr "Pour davantage d'informations, voir <ulink url=\"&commongatewayinterface;\">Common Gateway Interface</ulink>, <ulink url=\"&theapachesoftwarefoundation;\">The Apache Software Foundation</ulink> et <ulink url=\"&javascript;\">JavaScript</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30935
msgid "Searching \"CGI tutorial\" on Google by typing encoded URL <ulink url=\"&httpwwwgooglecomutfiqcgitutorial;\">http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;q=CGI+tutorial</ulink> directly to the browser address is a good way to see the CGI script in action on the Google server."
msgstr "Rechercher «&nbsp;CGI tutorial&nbsp;» sur Google en entrant l’URL encodée <ulink url=\"&httpwwwgooglecomutfiqcgitutorial;\">http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;q=CGI+tutorial</ulink> directement dans la barre d'adresse du navigateur est une bonne méthode pour voir un script CGI en action sur le serveur Google."

